ENTRY       EC 4.2.2.15                 Enzyme
NAME        anhydrosialidase;
            anhydroneuraminidase;
            sialglycoconjugate N-acylneuraminylhydrolase (2,7-cyclizing);
            sialidase L
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Acting on polysaccharides
SYSNAME     glycoconjugate sialyl-lyase (2,7-cyclizing)
REACTION    Elimination of alpha-sialyl groups in N-acetylneuraminic acid glycosides, releasing 2,7-anhydro-alpha-N-acetylneuraminate
COMMENT     Also acts on N-glycolylneuraminate glycosides. cf. EC 3.2.1.18 (exo-alpha-sialidase) and EC 3.2.1.129 (endo-alpha-sialidase).
HISTORY     EC 4.2.2.15 created 1992 as EC 3.2.1.138, transferred 2003 to EC 4.2.2.15
REFERENCE   1  [PMID:2254319]
  AUTHORS   Li YT, Nakagawa H, Ross SA, Hansson GC, Li SC.
  TITLE     A novel sialidase which releases 2,7-anhydro-alpha-N-acetylneuraminic acid from sialoglycoconjugates.
  JOURNAL   J. Biol. Chem. 265 (1990) 21629-33.
  ORGANISM  Macrobdella decora
